    public class AssertMaybe<T>
extends org.assertj.core.api.AbstractAssert<AssertMaybe<T>,io.reactivex.Maybe>
    AssertJ Assert class for Maybe. Uses TestSubscriber from Rx to subscribe to Maybe and perform assertions on the results.

      • after

        public AssertMaybe<T> after(long duration,
                            java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit)
        If a TestScheduler is provided, advanced the time by the specified duration. Throws an IllegalStateException if there is no TestScheduler provided. Use assertThat(Maybe, TestScheduler) to construct an AssertMaybe instance that can be used for async testing.
        Parameters:
        duration - the time duration
        timeUnit - the time unit of the duration
        Returns:
        the AssertMaybe instance.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if called when no test scheduler was provided
